Jupyter notebooks

Jupyter notebooks#

Working with Jupyter notebooks is great for learning gdsfactory as well as running heavy simulations on Cloud servers.

Thanks to kweb you can use the webapp version on klayout in your browser or inside jupyter notebooks.

[1]:

import kweb.server_jupyter as kj  # requires `pip install gdsfactory[full]` or `pip install kweb`
import gdsfactory as gf

gf.config.rich_output()
PDK = gf.get_generic_pdk()
PDK.activate()

gf.config.set_log_level("DEBUG")
kj.start()

2023-02-20 18:00:37.512 | INFO     | gdsfactory.technology.layer_views:__init__:785 - Importing LayerViews from YAML file: /home/runner/work/gdsfactory/gdsfactory/gdsfactory/generic_tech/layer_views.yaml.
2023-02-20 18:00:37.519 | INFO     | gdsfactory.pdk:activate:206 - 'generic' PDK is now active
